OL,3,CCampaigners call for better food
OL,4,Callergy protection in the Channel
OL,5,CIslands
OL,7,FThe parents of Natasha Ednan-
OL,8,FLaperouse, who died aged 15 from a
OL,9,Fsevere allergic reaction to sesame,
OL,10,Fare visiting Jersey to call for better
OL,11,Fprotection for people with food
OL,12,Fallergies in the Channel Islands.
OL,14,FTanya and Nadim Ednan-Laperouse OBEs
OL,15,Ffounded The Natasha Allergy Research
OL,16,FFoundation after their daughter's
OL,17,Fdeath and are speaking at the first
OL,18,Fever Food Allergy Conference in Jersey.
